---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTAButton from '../components/CTAButton.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="MMTUK"
  description="Real Resource Economics and Modern Monetary Theory — the relationship to MMTUK."
>
  <h1>MMTUK</h1>

  <h2 class="!mt-10">Real Resource Economics and MMT</h2>
  <p>
    Real Resource Economics builds on the operational insights of Modern
    Monetary Theory (MMT): once you understand that a currency-issuing
    government is never financially constrained, the real questions become
    questions about resources — labour, materials, energy, time — and what we
    choose to do with them. <em>[Placeholder.]</em>
  </p>

  <h2>About MMTUK</h2>
  <p>
    MMTUK is the United Kingdom's first MMT-driven policy research
    organisation. It produces policy papers, briefings, and analysis that apply
    MMT to UK fiscal, monetary, and employment policy. Its flagship work
    includes detailed proposals for a UK Job Guarantee.
  </p>

  <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
    <CTAButton href="https://mmtuk.org" external>
      Visit MMTUK
    </CTAButton>
    <CTAButton href="https://mmtuk.org/policy-papers/" external variant="outline">
      MMTUK Policy Papers
    </CTAButton>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
